product_title: Braun Travel Alarm Clock - BNC-5
review_headline: Braun Travel Alarm Door Falls Off
review_body: The clock is great as the past Braun alarms have been but the door has fallen away from its pins. We are very careful with it and have never dropped it or abused it but the tiny pin that is lodged into the housing of the clock pulled away because the plastic area where the pins are attached failed and the small hole that holds one of the pins is now a slot so the pin slips out and the door falls off. I will not buy this product again due to the defect in manufacturing. There must be a better way to keep the door on the clock.

Also if you search the model number for the "kids" watch it will show up twice, labeled as a kids watch and as a men's watch.

In short, I think it would be fine for a kid 10 years or older. A younger child may have too much of the band overhanging.

product_title: Casio Men's MRW200H-1EV Dive Watch with Black Band
review_headline: Good: It works great as a watch
review_body:
I wish I could give this 3.5 stars.

Good: It works great as a watch. Despite whatever any other complaints I have of it, I've worn it doing tons of different activities and its survived just fine. I've showered with it on accident, done dishes, etc, and it hasn't worn down too bad yet, nor had component failure. Have had it 2 months and haven't had to correct the time yet. That's pretty solid for $12 Casio.

The bad: The band is super cheap; which was to be expected because, surprise!, so was the watch. In fact, the whole watch looks a little dinky upon close inspection. Looks good from far but far from pretty.

Overall; I got what I expected.

product_title: Casio Men's PRW-3500-1CR Atomic Resin Digital Watch
review_body: Disappointing!  After receiving the watch, reading the manual, and setting the city and Day Light Savings Time.  The auto setting for Day Light Savings time did not work.  The watch also was turned toward the west sun for 4 to 5 hours for two straight days, yet it never left M (medium power setting) designation for the solar battery. product_title: Casio Men's STB-1000-1CF OmniSync Sports Gear Bluetooth Fitness Smartwatch
review_body:
Shame on Amazon - I initially could not pair the watch because it was already paired with "Julie's iPhone". I had to deleter the previous pairing in order to pair my phone with the watch. The phone also had various information saved on it from "Julie". The watch arrived loose in the box (out of it's holder and retail box). There was no lens protector (peel off film) that a new watch would have had. The watch was clearly USED, not new. Amazon is not advertising this item as used, so BEWARE! I expected a new product, otherwise I would have ordered it from WalMart.
Now, about the watch - The watch works as advertised (other than having to clear someone else's data off it), and I am very happy with it's operation. It stays paired and gives me all the notifications on my iPhone 6 (IOS 9 Beta). Nice watch, but thanks to Amazon, I took away 2 stars. Order this product if you want a "USED" watch!

review_body: Dakota claims to have excellent warranties, but not so.  I received one of these watches for Xmas a few years ago, and the first time I took it diving, the crystal came off the front, and thus the inner workings rusted. The watch was supposed to be waterproof.  When making a claim, I was told:  (1) no matter how I received the watch, I needed to prove purchase before they would warrant; and (2) only the inner workings of the watch are covered by warranty, with the crystal NOT covered at all, so they would charge $20 to repair. review_headline: Great for taking vital sign measurements using the second hand
review_body: I'm preparing to do my clinical rotation next month and this is a great, inexpensive watch for me to help take vital signs manually, such as tracking  pulse and respiration measurements using the second hand.  The interface of the watch is big and clear so I can keep track of the seconds without having to squint my eyes closely at the watch.  In addition, the company was very responsive when I reported that my watch had a stain on the interface, which they quickly replaced for me with a new one that came in a week later.  The band is kind of stiff, however the resourcefulness of the watch to help me take manual vital sign measurements is more of an important purchasing factor for me.

product_title: Invicta Men's 8926OB Pro Diver Stainless Steel Automatic Watch with Link Bracelet
review_headline: Worth the money, be careful with the glass.
review_body:
Alrighty, after seeking out the ultimate low-profile, ultra water resistant, mechanical watch with a rotating bezel and date for less than $100, I settled on this.

It looks much like the famous Rolex Submariner, and performs similarly.

However, after about a year of use now, the paint on the bezel is chipping, and after a decent smack on the hood of a car the crystal has cracked and all but shattered.

It keeps time fairly well, gaining about 15 seconds per day, without taking it to a healer for fine tuning.

review_headline: ... been wearing this watch for several months and I love it. It's a great weight and isn't too ...
review_body: I've been wearing this watch for several months and I love it. It's a great weight and isn't too heavy. The face is striking and easily readable, with the mother of pearl adding a nice touch. I've worn it underwater many times while swimming this summer with no moisture leaking in. The bubble over the date took a bit to get used to, but now I can read the date without issues. Easily adjusted to the correct size for me. The clasp feels secure and I haven't noticed it opening at all. I have noticed a bit of the rose gold finish wearing off where my wrist rests on tabletops, but it's not noticeable to anyone but me. Great watch, would buy again!

product_title: Kenneth Cole New York Men's KC9260 Dress Sport Rose Gold Bezel Men's Bracelet Watch
review_body: Beautiful watch.  I own several Kenneth Cole watches in different styles, and this is one of my favorites.  The dial is easy to read and while I typically wear reading glasses,  I am able to read the day/date hands without them.  Besides a wedding band, watches are the only "jewelry" that I wear.  This one fills the bill as both an attractive and functional timepiece. The only negative comment I would share, and the reason I give it 4 stars instead of 5 relates to the description which indicates that this watch has a "21-jewel, Japanese quartz analog automatic movement, with exhibition case back".  It is a Japanese quartz movement but does not have an exhibition case back, nor an automatic (self-winding) movement.

review_body: Like everyone else has mentioned, these just aren't quality screwdrivers.  If what you're really using them for is for repairing watches, save up and get Bergeons.  That's not meant to be an elitist statement; these just really don't work.  The bits had already fallen out or fell out soon after they arrived for most of these.  One was missing both set screws, and the others only had one installed, which also meant that the blades don't stay coaxial to the handle.  It's very easy to scratch a watch when one of these decides to drop its blade, and no amount of tightening seems to fix them.

review_headline: Beautiful face, but cheap sounding links

Beautiful watch face. The band looks nice all around. The links do make that squeaky cheapo noise when you swing it back and forth on your wrist which can be embarrassing in front of watch enthusiasts. However, to the naked eye from afar, you can't tell the links are cheap or folded because it is well polished and brushed and the folds are pretty tight for the most part.

I love the new member of my collection and it looks great. I've had it for about a week and so far it has kept good time despite day 1 which is typical of a new mechanical watch

product_title: Orient Men's CEM65005D 'Blue Mako' Automatic Dive Watch With Black Rubber Band
review_headline: Love the watch, hate the band
review_body:
This automatic watch keeps great time when worn regularly or placed on a winder. Holds time for at least 48 hours. It looks great....face is a darker blue than pictured under normal light conditions, but a bright blue in direct sunlight. The upper crown controls only the day of week, which can be set in English or Spanish. The upper crown screws down, but not as securely as the main crown.

My only knock is that the band pinches the skin and hair on my wrist... plus it has that unsightly dolphin emblem. Do yourself a favor and either buy this watch with the metal band or replace the one that comes with it. I replaced it with a metal band for less money than it would have cost to buy it that way.

product_title: SE 16 PCS Watch Tool Kit
review_headline: Does it's job well.  Some flimsy parts.
review_body:
Worked really well. I had to remove a few links from a newly purchased Invicta watch. Sure, I could go out to the garage and find a nail set and some pliers, but I'd just spent over $100 on a watch and didn't want to scratch it up. So, I bought this and it made life a lot easier.

One critical note: The piece that lets you set your watch band in it and screw the pin out is very flimsy. Mine had two plastic pieces on either end that promptly fell right off and I had to glue them back on. Without those pieces, the whole knob falls apart and can't be used for removing pins. It was an easy fix, but annoying.

product_title: Seiko Men's SNZH53 Seiko 5 Automatic Dark Blue Dial Stainless Steel Watch
review_body: The SNZH53 is a very good automatic watch at its price point. It keeps good time, has a decent power reserve and the deep blue of the face and bezel is very pretty. The crystal is fairly scratch resistant. Not as good as high end watches, but the hardlex will prevent all but the hardest bangs from leaving a mark. The worst thing about this watch is the bracelet. It feels light and cheap. If you're planning to wear it on an aftermarket strap, as I do, that's not an issue. Though it's a "divers watch" it doesn't have a screw-down crown so it's not really great for doing a lot of underwater wear. That said, I've gone swimming with it on and had no ill effects.

product_title: Seiko Men's SSC203 Analog Display Japanese Quartz Silver Watch
review_body:
The watch is heavy on my wrist, and there is no back light or glow making it difficult to read in low light. After 3 weeks of normal wear a chip developed on the edge of my glass, humidity and moisture then condensed on the inside of my watch face and then it stopped running all together. Normally I would give this one star, but I contacted the warranty folks and they had me send it in for repair or replacement. I have not receieved the watch back yet, and so I may change this to one star eventually. The other knock I have is on how easily the 'ring around the face' scratches. I had this out of the box for 24 hours, just wearing it around the house and somehow it picked up a scratch on the ring.

That being said, I do like the styling.

product_title: Timex Unisex Weekender Analog Quartz Watch
review_headline: I still haven't found a design I like better, so I'll keep going with them
review_body: I'm on my third now after the first two failed. The crown on the first fell off, and water got inside the 2nd which eventually caused it to stop working. The description is confusing because it says water resistant to 99ft which is a conflicting statement. Resistance means it can survive incidental water, but a depth rating implies waterproofness, which it clearly doesn't have. I still haven't found a design I like better, so I'll keep going with them, but wish it were truly waterproof.

product_title: Victorinox Men's 241678.1 Analog Display Swiss Quartz Black Watch
review_headline: Good brand, but two flaws with the model...
review_body: Interesting, military-inspired design but the watch -- as sold -- has two flaws: 1) the luminous material used on the hands and small hour markers is inferior (very weak) and 2) the thick nylon band is uncomfortable and increases the thickness of the watch significantly. I own and have owned many Victorinox watches and they are typically excellent. I won't hesitate to purchase this brand again -- just not this particular model.
